                <head>No. 396.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Curry</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 6, 1886</date>. (Received October
                        6.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Curry informs Mr. Bayard that the collection of discriminating duties will
                    continue as in the past on the products of foreign countries which are shipped
                    to Cuba and Porto Rico from ports of the United States.</p>
            </div>
